  "prompt": "Where can someone find a free good virtual piano keyboard that displays the music sheets upon the keyboard?",
  "response": "There are several online tools and websites where you can find virtual piano keyboards that display music sheets. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Virtual Piano** - Virtual Piano offers an online piano keyboard where you can learn to play piano. It has various features including displaying sheet music. You can access it at: [virtualpiano.net](https://virtualpiano.net)\n\n2. **Piano Marvel** - Piano Marvel provides a virtual piano keyboard along with sheet music and interactive lessons. This tool is mainly geared towards learning, and it has a free trial option. You can find it at: [pianomarvel.com](https://www.pianomarvel.com)\n\n3. **NoteFlight** - NoteFlight offers online music notation software that can connect with a virtual piano keyboard for interactive learning and playing. The basic version is free, and you can access it at: [noteflight.com](https://www.noteflight.com)\n\n4. **Online Pianist** - Online Pianist allows you to play piano online and displays sheet music while you play. You can check it out at: [onlinepianist.com](https://www.onlinepianist.com)\n\n5. **Musycom** - Musycom has a virtual piano with simple sheet music displayed above the keyboard. It's free and easy to use for beginners. You can access it at: [musycom.com](https://www.musycom.com)\n\nRemember to check the specific features and user reviews to ensure they meet your learning needs and preferences.",
